---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is WO a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL (5 Points)"
  description="WO is valid in SOWPODS (Collins) but NOT in TWL. Worth 5 points (W=4, O=1), WO is an archaic exclamation of grief or woe. Check your dictionary before playing."
  keywords="is wo a scrabble word, wo scrabble valid, wo sowpods, wo twl invalid, two letter w words scrabble, wo definition scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article", "headline": "Is WO a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL (5 Points)", "description": "WO is valid in SOWPODS (Collins) but NOT in TWL. Worth 5 points, it's an archaic exclamation of grief. Dictionary-dependent validity.", "datePublished": "2026-06-23", "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" }, "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" }, "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-wo-a-scrabble-word" } })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [ { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is WO a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "WO is valid ONLY in SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words). It is NOT valid in TWL (Tournament Word List) used in North American NASPA play." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "What does WO mean?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "WO is an archaic exclamation expressing grief or sorrow, a variant spelling of 'woe.' It appeared in Middle English texts and was retained in Collins Scrabble Words." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many points is WO worth in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "WO is worth 5 points: W(4) + O(1) = 5. The high-value W tile makes this a decent-scoring 2-letter play in SOWPODS games." } } ] })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Validity</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is WO a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">WO is an archaic cry of sorrow — think medieval poets lamenting their fate. In modern Scrabble, it's a dictionary-dependent play that scores a solid 5 points in SOWPODS but gets you challenged off the board in TWL. Here's when to play it and when to hold back.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-orange-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-950/30 to-red-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-orange-500/70">⚠️ Dictionary-Dependent</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">WO</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-orange-300 font-semibold mb-3">5 points · W(4) + O(1) · Archaic exclamation of grief · SOWPODS only</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">WO is valid in Collins Scrabble Words (international) but INVALID in TWL (North America). An archaic variant of "woe" expressing grief.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-orange-500/30 bg-orange-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-400">5</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-red-400">✗</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Invalid in TWL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">✓</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid in SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-400">W</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">4-Point Tile</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What Does WO Mean?</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">📖 Definition</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">WO is an <span class="text-white font-medium">archaic exclamation of grief or sorrow</span>, a shortened form of "woe." Found in Middle English texts and early modern literature (e.g., Chaucer's Canterbury Tales). It expressed deep sadness or lamentation. Collins retained it as a valid entry reflecting historical English usage.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Dictionary Comparison</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ INVALID in TWL (NASPA)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Not in Tournament Word List. Playing WO in North American tournaments results in challenge loss and tile recall.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Valid in SOWPODS (Collins)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Accepted in Collins. Legal in international, UK, Australian tournaments and all SOWPODS-based online games.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">When to Play WO</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SOWPODS confirmed:</span> If the game uses Collins dictionary, WO is safe. Five points from 2 tiles — use it freely on premium squares.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">W tile dump:</span> The W is worth 4 points but hard to use in short words. WO gives you a quick exit when better options aren't available.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">When in doubt — play WE:</span> WE scores 5 points and is valid in BOTH dictionaries. Same score, zero risk. Always prefer WE over WO.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Safe W Alternatives (Both Dictionaries)</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WO</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">5pts ⚠️</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WOE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WOW</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WAX</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts ✓</span></span>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-ew-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is EW a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS-Only Exclamation</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-na-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is NA a Scrabble Word? Valid in Both Dictionaries</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word's validity in both TWL and SOWPODS — free, instant, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
